          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-15 16:43:18" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of {L:ὀνομάζω&lt;SDBG:ὀνομάζω:000001&gt;}[b] ‘to call a name,’ {D:33.133}) to be caused to be made known</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to be known</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It would be possible, however, to interpret ὀνομάζομαι in {S:04501502000014} in a more literal sense, so that one could translate the final part of the verse as ‘where the name of Christ had not been used’ or ‘where no one had spoken the name of Christ.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
